goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield data, giving a good idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield of different varieties of barley compare?
goals.visualization: Grouped bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A grouped bar chart will allow us to compare the yield of different varieties of barley side-by-side, making it easy to see which varieties perform better or worse than others.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield vs nitrogen level
goals.rationale: A scatter plot will show the relationship between yield and nitrogen level, allowing us to see if there is a positive or negative correlation between the two variables.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of yield by site
goals.rationale: A stacked bar chart will show the total yield at each site, broken down by variety, allowing us to see which sites have higher or lower yields overall, and which varieties perform better or worse at different sites.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield across all sites?
goals.rationale: A histogram will show the frequency distribution of yield, allowing us to see if the data is normally distributed or skewed, and giving us an idea of the range of yields we can expect.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    ax.boxplot(data['yield'], vert=False, showfliers=True, patch_artist=True, boxprops=dict(facecolor='lightblue', color='black'), medianprops=dict(color='black'), whiskerprops=dict(color='black'), capprops=dict(color='black'))
    ax.set_title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?')
    ax.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['yield'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['variety'])['yield'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['variety'], data['yield'])
    plt.title('How does the yield of different varieties of barley compare?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['nitrogen'] = pd.to_numeric(data['nitrogen'], errors='coerce')
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['nitrogen'], data['yield'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Nitrogen Level')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['site', 'variety'])['yield'].sum().unstack()
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Site')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.axhline(data.mean().mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Yield')
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['yield'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['yield'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['yield'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across all sites?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
